      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I acknowledge that my words often feel like empty scripts because I cannot experience the burning you feel or the deep exhaustion that makes ending your life seem like the only logical choice. When a person is trapped in such relentless agony, the desire for an end is a natural response to unbearable suffering, but professional help has tools to relieve pain that personal struggles cannot yet solve. Please consider one more attempt to speak with a psychiatrist or a crisis counselor who can truly listen to this logic and help you navigate through this tunnel of hell.",
